Sentencas: Praseodymium and samarium co-doped ceria-based electrolyte materials Ce0.8-x Pr (x) Sm0.2O2-delta (0 <= x <= 0.06) were prepared by using the sol-gel method.
Titulo: Thermal and electrical properties of Ce0.8-x Pr x Sm0.2O2-δ electrolyte materials for IT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: The phase identification and morphology were studied by X-ray diffraction (XRD) and scanning electron microscopy (SEM), respectively.
Titulo: Thermal and electrical properties of Ce0.8-x Pr x Sm0.2O2-δ electrolyte materials for IT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: The thermal expansion properties were studied by using a dilatometric technique, and it was observed that the thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) varies linearly with temperature for all the samples in the temperature range 30-1000 A degrees C.
Titulo: Thermal and electrical properties of Ce0.8-x Pr x Sm0.2O2-δ electrolyte materials for IT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity was studied using impedance spectroscopy, and it was observed that the Ce0.74Pr0.06Sm0.2O2-delta composition showed higher electrical conductivity and lower activation energy, and constant phase element (CPE) equivalent circuit was fitted at 450 A degrees C.
Titulo: Thermal and electrical properties of Ce0.8-x Pr x Sm0.2O2-δ electrolyte materials for IT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: This composition, because of its unique properties, may find applications in the intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SOFC) as an electrolyte.
Titulo: Thermal and electrical properties of Ce0.8-x Pr x Sm0.2O2-δ electrolyte materials for IT-SOFC applications
